Patients at Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center in New York treated patients with advanced melanoma . 
  The 49-year-old woman developed a huge tumour underneath her left breast . 
  She was given a new combination of two drugs to treat skin cancer - ipilimumab and nivolumab . 
  61 per cent of patients treated with the combination showed significant tumour shrinkage . 
  Doctors said her recovery was 'one of the most astonishing responses' they have ever seen . 
 